OL,3,CMet chief: Violence against women
OL,4,Cshould be treated the 'same as
OL,5,Cterrorism'
OL,7,FCombatting violence against women and
OL,8,Fgirls will need the same level of
OL,9,Ffunding as the fights against
OL,10,Fterrorism or organised crime, the UK's
OL,11,Fmost senior police officer has said.
OL,13,FSir Mark Rowley told the London
OL,14,FPolicing Board there are hundreds of
OL,15,Fthousands of men in Britain who are a
OL,16,Fthreat to women and girls and the
OL,17,Fscale of the problem means it has to
OL,18,Fbe treated as a threat to national
OL,19,Fsecurity.
